{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-markdown-post-js","path":"/docs/userguide/hello_world/","webpackCompilationHash":"1b57748ccaed9fefb8c4","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"http://local:8000","title":"BioDynaMO Website","description":"Everything you need to know about biology simulations."}},"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Hello World","date":"2019-01-01","date_pretty":"01 January, 2019","path":"/docs/userguide/hello_world/","meta_title":"BioDynaMo User Guide","meta_description":"This is the hello world page.","image":"","next":{"url":"/docs/userguide/hello_world/","title":"Hello World","description":"This is the hello world page."},"sidebar":"userguide","toc":true},"html":"<p>The most basic BioDynaMo simulation (i.e. our Hello World program) is a\nstatic single cell. It is the default model that comes with the installation of\nBioDynaMo. In this section we shall go over the three simple steps of running\nthis simple simulation.</p>\n<h2 id=\"step-1-create-your-simulation\"><a href=\"#step-1-create-your-simulation\" aria-label=\"step 1 create your simulation permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Step 1: Create your simulation</h2>\n<p>Run the following command to create a new project called \"hello_world\":</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">biodynamo new hello_world</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"step-2-build-your-simulation\"><a href=\"#step-2-build-your-simulation\" aria-label=\"step 2 build your simulation permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Step 2: Build your simulation</h2>\n<p>Go into the newly created directory <code class=\"language-text\">hello_world</code> with:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">cd</span> hello_world</code></pre></div>\n<p>And build the project files with:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">biodynamo build</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"step-3-run-your-simulation\"><a href=\"#step-3-run-your-simulation\" aria-label=\"step 3 run your simulation permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Step 3: Run your simulation</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">biodynamo run</code></pre></div>\n<p>You should see \"Simulation completed succesfully\" as the output.</p>\n<h2 id=\"extra-cell-division\"><a href=\"#extra-cell-division\" aria-label=\"extra cell division permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Extra: Cell division</h2>\n<p>Let's make the simulation more interesting by adding a biological behavior to the\ncell: cell division. Open the <code class=\"language-text\">src/hello_world.h</code> and add the following line to\nthe simulate function after the cell is created.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"cpp\"><pre class=\"language-cpp\"><code class=\"language-cpp\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Add the biological behavior to the cell.</span>\ncell<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">AddBiologyModule</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token function\">GrowDivide</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">32</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">3000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>gAllEventIds<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Rebuild and rerun the simulation to have the cell division take effect. visit the\nnext exercise to learn about the visualization features of BioDynaMo.</p>\n<a class=\"sbox\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <div class=\"sbox-content\">\n    \t<h4><b>Info</b></h4>\n    \t<p>You might want to run for a few more simulation steps to witness cells dividing\n\t\t</p>\n    </div>\n</a>","fields":{"slug":"/docs/userguide/hello_world/"},"timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"The most basic BioDynaMo simulation (i.e. our Hello World program) is a\nstatic single cell. It is the default model that comes with theâ€¦","fileAbsolutePath":"/website/content/biodynamo/doc/user_guide/hello_world.md"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/docs/userguide/hello_world/"}}}